 Stretch.";i:23;s:131:"The next pose in the yoga for seniors sequence is the cat-cow stretch which arches and rounds the spine while breathing in and out.";i:24;s:53:"It stretches the spine abdominals shoulders and hips.";i:25;s:95:"Hence the pose is recommended for improving spinal flexibility digestion and muscular strength.";i:26;s:77:"With all of that said here are some examples of chair yoga poses for seniors.";i:27;s:34:"Extend arms straight into the air.";i:28;s:49:"Press palms together forming the tip of a candle.";i:29;s:20:"Hold for 30 seconds.";i:30;s:34:"Extend arms straight into the air.";i:31;s:35:"If possible extend legs forward as.";i:32;s:102:"Yoga for Seniors Chair Stretches for Pain Relief Relaxation Joint Health Flexibility Stress - YouTube.";i:33;s:82:"Seated Yoga is essentially modified yoga that can be done while seated in a chair.";i:34;s:132:"These adaptations make yoga realizable for individuals who cannot stand or have challenges moving for standing to a seated position.";i:35;s:172:"While seated in a chairwheelchair I will show you how seniors can retain the basic fundamentals of yoga allowing for stretches of their hips back spine twist and breathing.";i:36;s:92:"To perform this yoga pose sit on the edge of your chair with your feet shoulder width apart.";i:37;s:94:"When you inhale slowly lift your arms upward and imagine that you are reaching to the ceiling.";i:38;s:66:"Press your palms together and hold for the duration of the inhale.";i:39;s:20:"This ones a win-win.";i:40;s:62:"Build confidence and get a full-body stretch at the same time.";i:41;s:34:"Sit tall at the edge of your seat.";i:42;s:116:"Bend your right knee to the side and stretch your left leg out behind you as you press down through your outer heel.";i:43;s:37:"Hold for five breaths then repeat on.";i:44;s:39:"Standing and Balance Poses for Seniors.";i:45;s:111:"All yoga poses promote balance but some especially some standing postures require special attention to balance.";i:46;s:113:"Often this is done in the act of rising from a floor pose but you can also step into it from a standing position.";i:47;s:87:"Chair yoga for seniors is a great way to overcome many age-related issues and ailments.";i:48;s:74:"The stretches are performed with the balance safety of sitting in a chair.";i:49;s:107:"As you age you might have more time to take care of yourself and do the things that make you happy in life.";i:50;s:32:"Chair yoga Yoga is for everyone.";i:51;s:28:"Any age or state of fitness.";i:52;s:49:"Yoga can calm your mind and strengthen your body.";i:53;s:49:"These chair poses can be done at work or at home.";i:54;s:79:"Directions Most positions begin using the same seated position called Sit tall.";i:55;s:90:"Sit in a chair with feet planted firmly on the floor Back straight to elongate your spine.";i:56;s:78:"By using a chair yoga for seniors becomes more safe and builds confidence too.";i:57;s:116:"Traditional yoga poses like mountain pose can be adapted as a foundation posture in chair yoga for seniors routines.";i:58;s:80:"Chair yoga should always feel comfortable and within a persons personal ability.";i:59;s:106:"Chair Yoga Sequence for Seniors Many senior citizens practice yoga regularly for a healthy and happy life.";i:60;s:90:"Some may not be medically fit to stand or fatigue out if they stand for elongated periods.";i:61;s:126:"As a yoga teacher you may use the senior yoga sequences for the elderly who want to practice but are unable to stand for long.";i:62;s:16:"Are You In Pain.";i:63;s:22:"What is a Pain Doctor.";i:64;s:24:"What is Pain Management.";i:65;s:19:"Acute Chronic Pain.";i:66;s:131:"All yoga poses have modifications and people with inflexibility injuries or limited mobility can all engage in specific yoga poses.";i:67;s:75:"In fact you can perform a wide variety of yoga poses straight from a chair.";i:68;s:80:"Everyone gets something out of yoga but the people who benefit most are seniors.";i:69;s:113:"The reason for this is because elderly people use the brains two hemispheres more equally than younger people do.";i:70;s:37:"Chair yoga for seniors popular poses.";i:71;s:41:"Chair yoga safely improves senior health.";i:72;s:102:"This 17 min practice invites awareness and integrity into the body specifically the line of the spine.";i:73;s:68:"Below are 10 chair yoga poses to get you started with this practice.";i:74;s:42:"A healthier stronger and more relaxed you.";i:75;s:180:"Chair yoga routines or wheelchair yoga poses only require a sturdy chair for an elderly person to receive the benefits of yoga without needing to stand or perform complex postures.";i:76;s:154:"However before beginning wheelchair yoga exercises or any other wheelchair exercises for seniors on a regular basis always be sure to consult your doctor.";}}